Subject: [PATCH] feat(article-50-kit): wire /article-50-kit to
 meok-watermark-attest-mcp
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The /article-50-kit landing page (live at csoai-v2-app.vercel.app) was
a 97-line Stripe-checkout-only stub. The £999 Kit is the highest-revenue
single-product surface in the CSOAI stack, and the page was under-
delivering on the Article 50 cliff story.

This commit wires the page to the real meok-watermark-attest-mcp on
PyPI (v1.3.10) — a working MCP, not a PDF. Differentiation over
the 19+ 'compliance kits' in the market.

WHAT SHIPS:

1. Live days-to-cliff counter (51 days from 2026-06-12, updates every
   60s) — replaces the stale '52 Days Left' hardcoded text. The
   hardcoded number was a 1-day drift off the actual cliff.

2. 5 Article 50 obligations in scope (50(1) chatbot disclosure, 50(2)
   synthetic content watermarking C2PA-2.0, 50(3) emotion recognition
   + biometric, 50(4) deepfake, 50(5) AI-text public interest) with
   fine per obligation (€35M or 7% global turnover).

3. The Differentiation card: 9 MCP tools surfaced from the PyPI
   source (classify_obligations, generate_disclosure_text,
   audit_content_pipeline, sign_watermark_attestation,
   c2pa_generate_manifest, c2pa_validate_manifest,
   get_deadline_status, check_access, _shared_check_access). Plus
   the one-click 'pip install meok-watermark-attest-mcp' button with
   clipboard copy.

4. 5 surfaces × 5 languages matrix: 25 cells, one MCP call each.
   Surfaces: UI banner, API response, TTS opening, C2PA manifest,
   capability description. Languages: en/fr/de/es/it. Visualised as
   a green-dot matrix.

5. What's in the £999 Kit (6 components): transparency docs + risk
   classification + MCP Pro tier (12 mo) + C2PA manifest templates +
   25-language disclosure library + post-market plan.

6. 3-tier pricing: Free (£0, 10 audits/day) / Kit (£999 one-time) /
   Assessment (£4,950). Each tier wires to a canonical Stripe link
   from the meok-attestation-api ladder (plink_8k91F / 8k91H / 8k91G).
   Pro £199/mo for ongoing compliance is in the footer.

7. Sources of truth footer: EU AI Act implementation tracker
   (artificialintelligenceact.eu/transparency-rules-article-50/) +
   HSFKramer + TwoBirds analyses + the Digital Omnibus context. The
   page now anchors its claim to the regulation text, not to a
   secondary source.

WHY THIS IS LOAD-BEARING:

- Article 50 cliff is 51 days out (2 Aug 2026, verified against
  artificialintelligenceact.eu + 3 legal analyses). The Digital
  Omnibus delayed high-risk Annex III to 2 Dec 2027 but did NOT
  touch Article 50. The £999 Kit is the cliff-surfing revenue
  surface; the page is the conversion point.
- 30+ other CSOAI surfaces say 'August 2, 2026' for Article 50 (all
  correct). The meok-watermark-attest-mcp README + PyPI summary
  said '2 November 2026' (wrong, hotfixed in PR-HOTFIX-1 at
  bef9140). The /article-50-kit page is RIGHT; this commit wires
  it to the right MCP.
- The 'differentiation' is the load-bearing claim: most compliance
  kits ship PDFs, this ships a working MCP. The 9 tools + the 5×5
  matrix are the proof.

FALLBACK BEHAVIOR:

The /api/checkout endpoint may return 503 (the page handles this).
On network error, the page falls back to direct Stripe links (the
canonical plink_... ladder). The £999 Kit button works whether
the /api/checkout is online or not.

Files: 1, +266/-45 lines. Branch: feat/article-50-mcp-wire.

LIVE: https://csoai-v2-app.vercel.app/article-50-kit (after Vercel
rebuild). Local verify: csoai-org-v2/src/app/article-50-kit/page.tsx.

